# BCD Code Style Guide and Conventions

* Use a beautify package e.g. for Atom https://github.com/Glavin001/atom-beautify and/or Prettier e.g. https://atom.io/packages/prettier-atom
* use uppercase variable names for all const decalrations.




## File Naming
* All javascript files' names should use lowercase seperated by hyphens



## Code comments
* Adopt  [Comment Showing Intent](https://standards.mousepawmedia.com/csi.html)
* Additional reading [on commenting]](https://dev.to/codemouse92/to-comment-or-not-to-comment-3f7h)


## Human readability and good code structuring practices
* Adopt [Human readable JS](https://dev.to/laurieontech/human-readable-javascript-337o)
* Use [loose principles](https://dev.to/codemouse92/clean-dry-solid-spaghetti-1lgm)
* Adopt [good habits](https://dev.to/mohanarpit/coding-practices-your-future-self-will-love-you-for-ohe)
